WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:05.191 --> 02:07.125
I'm Willie Dixon.

02:07.227 --> 02:09.627
And I'm making this here audio recording

02:09.729 --> 02:13.256
so that when you visit
Chess Recording Studio,

02:13.366 --> 02:15.334
you know the history.

02:15.435 --> 02:20.007
Now, the first time a gal took off her
underwear and threw them on stage

02:20.139 --> 02:23.202
it was on account of
a fella singing the blues.

02:23.309 --> 02:28.008
Now, when the white girls started doing it,
they called that rock and roll.

02:28.114 --> 02:32.278
Took a whole lot of people to make
the music that changed the world.

02:32.852 --> 02:35.946
Yes, sir. This story ain't just about me.

02:42.095 --> 02:44.256
<i>It all started with two men.</i>

02:45.632 --> 02:48.533
<i>One a white boy from Chicago.</i>

02:49.169 --> 02:51.330
Len, when are we getting married?

02:51.437 --> 02:52.768
<i>A witness for my Lord</i>

02:52.872 --> 02:56.137
<i>The other a sharecropper
from Mississippi.</i>

02:56.242 --> 02:58.836
<i>Say, who was a witness?</i>

02:58.945 --> 03:01.436
<i>The year was 1941.</i>

03:02.982 --> 03:05.143
<i>Say, Daniel was a witness</i>

03:06.953 --> 03:09.148
When are we getting married?

03:10.056 --> 03:11.353
I don't have the money.

03:11.457 --> 03:14.085
I told you I'd be fine without it.

03:15.328 --> 03:17.057
Well, I wouldn't.

03:18.631 --> 03:21.566
You don't know what it did to my father.

03:23.536 --> 03:25.800
I can't watch you go hungry.

03:39.085 --> 03:40.245
Da.

03:44.190 --> 03:46.522
Oh, how you doing, Mr. Feder?

03:46.893 --> 03:48.155
Hi, Dad.

03:53.433 --> 03:55.367
I want to marry her.

04:00.139 --> 04:01.401
Mr. Feder, I don't know if I told you,

04:01.507 --> 04:05.341
but I've been making plans to get out of
the junk business.

04:05.912 --> 04:08.039
I'm gonna open a club here.

04:09.849 --> 04:11.976
In the Negro neighborhood?

04:12.085 --> 04:14.110
Yeah. It's gonna be for Negroes.

04:14.220 --> 04:16.779
You're taking Shelly to Negro clubs?

04:18.891 --> 04:20.586
No, of course not.

04:21.527 --> 04:22.755
No, I'm just...

04:22.862 --> 04:26.263
I'd like you to know that
I'm making plans for the future.

04:26.366 --> 04:28.857
So, you are serious
about this marriage then?

04:28.968 --> 04:30.265
Yeah.

04:31.170 --> 04:32.398
I mean, when I can afford it.

04:32.505 --> 04:36.373
Your father and I, we come from
the same shithole in Poland.

04:37.310 --> 04:39.744
I didn't travel all this way

04:39.846 --> 04:43.873
to have my daughter marry some schmuck
from the same village.

04:45.718 --> 04:47.583
What did you say?

04:47.854 --> 04:49.344
- What did you say?
- Get in.

04:49.455 --> 04:50.752
Leonard.

04:52.659 --> 04:54.957
Don't worry where I'm from.

04:55.061 --> 04:57.723
My wife's gonna drive a Cadillac.

05:11.511 --> 05:13.604
Now, who is this here?

05:15.315 --> 05:17.545
Go on, get in the house now.

05:43.376 --> 05:45.344
McKinley Morganfield?

05:45.445 --> 05:46.412
Yes, sir?

05:46.512 --> 05:48.241
I'm Alan Lomax,

05:49.215 --> 05:51.615
and this is Mr. John Work
from Fisk University.

05:51.718 --> 05:54.084
- How you doing?
- Fine. You?

05:54.187 --> 05:57.748
I'm recording folk music
for the Library of Congress.

05:57.857 --> 05:58.949
Folk music?

06:00.727 --> 06:03.821
Could you move into the mike
a little bit for me? Thanks.

06:03.930 --> 06:05.795
Play that thing, man.

06:32.825 --> 06:35.225
That's what I sound like, huh?

06:35.328 --> 06:37.956
Yes, sir, that's what you sound like.

06:47.106 --> 06:50.337
Feel like I'm meeting myself
for the first time.

06:53.613 --> 06:57.310
<i>And he was. And he knew
it was a man he was meeting,</i>

06:58.151 --> 07:01.086
<i>too big for that slave
shack he was born in</i>

07:01.988 --> 07:04.548
<i>and too big for that plantation.</i>

07:19.572 --> 07:23.235
<i>Now, the acoustic guitar</i>
<i>was fine down south,</i>

07:23.342 --> 07:27.540
<i>because there's nothing but miles of</i>
<i>empty fields out your window.</i>

07:28.681 --> 07:33.482
<i>But in the city, with all
them streetcars and automobiles,</i>

07:34.253 --> 07:36.585
<i>you couldn't get yourself heard.</i>

07:38.090 --> 07:42.049
Hey, boy, ain't nobody want to hear
that sharecropping music.

07:43.262 --> 07:46.254
Take that shit back down there
to Mississippi.

07:50.703 --> 07:51.863
Hey.

07:51.971 --> 07:54.166
You're disturbing the peace!

08:02.615 --> 08:04.879
Why you want to cut me for, girl?

08:04.984 --> 08:08.385
You have been giving that same smile
to girls all morning.

08:08.488 --> 08:10.353
You must have three addresses
in your pocket.

08:10.456 --> 08:11.980
Addresses?

08:15.428 --> 08:16.622
No.

08:17.430 --> 08:19.955
- You're trouble. You know that?
- I know.

08:20.066 --> 08:21.658
How about you?

08:35.448 --> 08:38.746
You got to go, before my mama brings
the boys home. Come on.

08:38.851 --> 08:42.753
- Maybe those boys need a daddy.
- You're not daddy material.

08:45.224 --> 08:47.454
I'm not good enough for you?

08:51.531 --> 08:54.557
I don't talk as good as you
or something, huh?

08:55.401 --> 08:58.393
When I heard you start playing that music

08:59.705 --> 09:02.265
it took me someplace so good, Muddy.

09:02.808 --> 09:04.173
So good.

09:07.847 --> 09:09.542
Here you go, baby.

09:44.383 --> 09:46.817
Are you the owner of this club?

09:49.021 --> 09:50.352
Yes, I am.

09:50.856 --> 09:53.416
Isabella Allen. I make race records.

09:53.759 --> 09:56.353
Len Chess. How you doing? Wow.

09:56.462 --> 10:01.456
This is a beauty.
God, look at the lines on this thing.

10:01.867 --> 10:03.562
It's incredible.

10:04.203 --> 10:07.001
You can buy a car like this
making race records?

10:07.106 --> 10:09.301
If you find the right singer.

10:09.408 --> 10:12.844
Hey, I'd love to know
if you hear someone special.

10:13.779 --> 10:15.508
A record producer, huh?

10:15.615 --> 10:18.175
There'd be something in it for you.

10:18.985 --> 10:20.111
All right.

10:20.219 --> 10:22.779
Sweet. That's a beautiful car.

10:23.322 --> 10:25.347
You looking for girls?

10:26.359 --> 10:28.884
Excuse me? No, I'm opening a club.

10:28.995 --> 10:31.486
I don't mind you getting
men all liquored up

10:31.597 --> 10:34.327
but I lost two daughters to bluesmen.

10:34.433 --> 10:36.458
Dangerous business you in.

10:51.684 --> 10:53.584
What are you doing?

10:54.854 --> 10:59.018
<i>When Muddy met Little Walter,</i>
<i>he was just 17 years old,</i>

10:59.125 --> 11:02.424
<i>but he was the greatest harp
player that ever lived.</i>

11:02.528 --> 11:04.894
<i>That's it. That's all of it.</i>

11:08.267 --> 11:10.565
- Yeah, man.
- Play that for me.

11:19.578 --> 11:22.103
I'll give you $1
if you let me strum that guitar.

11:22.214 --> 11:23.613
I can busk more than your dollar.

11:23.716 --> 11:26.184
- I'll give you $2.
- You a headhunter?

11:26.285 --> 11:29.482
You fixing to chop my head off
with my own guitar? Man.

11:29.588 --> 11:32.022
Shit, you can't play better than me.

11:32.124 --> 11:34.285
Let me see the guitar, man.

12:15.267 --> 12:18.259
Hey, big guy,
your daddy sure can cook, huh?

12:19.038 --> 12:21.598
You're not gonna take care of Walter?

12:21.707 --> 12:23.231
Oh, I don't drink none of that.

12:23.342 --> 12:25.708
Good for you, Walter.
I'll make you a nice bath.

12:25.811 --> 12:27.745
Okay, thank you, ma'am.

12:27.847 --> 12:29.542
Why you got a gun?

12:29.915 --> 12:33.510
- In case in any good guys need shooting.
- You mean the bad guys?

12:36.322 --> 12:38.222
I is the bad guy.

12:40.493 --> 12:42.586
Hush now, scaring my boys,
and let me hear some of that harp.

12:42.695 --> 12:44.060
Okay, okay.

12:55.908 --> 12:57.068
Wait. Wait. Wait. Wait.

12:57.176 --> 12:58.609
- Where in the hell you going?
- Follow me now. Come on.

12:58.711 --> 13:02.272
No, no, no. No, look here.
You follow this guitar, son.

13:02.381 --> 13:03.678
"Son"?

13:05.985 --> 13:09.716
You can play the shit out of that guitar,
so I'll follow you anywhere you want,

13:11.257 --> 13:14.124
but don't you ever be
calling me no "son."

13:14.226 --> 13:15.488
Okay?

13:16.362 --> 13:19.889
- I don't need no daddy.
- No, boy, what you need is a mama.

13:19.999 --> 13:23.264
Someone who will feed you and clothe you

13:23.369 --> 13:25.837
and tell you to get
your behind in that bath.

13:25.938 --> 13:28.429
Well, you know what they say, now.

13:29.441 --> 13:31.466
A man can't have too many mamas.

13:31.577 --> 13:34.410
And you don't need this. You need soap.

13:40.886 --> 13:42.649
He fit me, Geneva.

13:43.522 --> 13:44.716
I heard.

13:47.126 --> 13:48.525
He fit me.

13:49.061 --> 13:50.892
<i>They was a family now.</i>

13:51.397 --> 13:54.366
<i>Little Walter, Muddy Waters</i>
<i>and Jimmy Rogers</i>

13:54.533 --> 13:57.400
<i>called themselves
"The All-Star Trio,"</i>

13:57.503 --> 14:00.836
<i>but everybody else knew</i>
<i>them as "The Headhunters"</i>

14:01.006 --> 14:03.668
<i>on account of how</i>
<i>they sliced their competition.</i>

14:05.177 --> 14:07.270
Will you help me out here?

14:13.719 --> 14:16.916
- Get your own gig, motherfucker!
- Let them play!

14:41.213 --> 14:43.477
- Get out of the way, Mud.
- Fucking son of a bitch!

14:43.582 --> 14:45.641
This is between me and this motherfucker.
Get out the way, Mud.

14:45.751 --> 14:47.844
- Son...
- I told you never to be calling me that.

14:47.953 --> 14:51.081
I know you did. But we family now.

14:51.190 --> 14:52.953
Then what the fuck you doing, Mud?

14:53.058 --> 14:54.787
Give me that pistol.

14:54.894 --> 14:58.762
I ain't trying to boss you.
But you're just too good to lose.

14:59.164 --> 15:03.533
We'll burn Chicago down if you don't
get your ass locked up or killed.

15:03.636 --> 15:06.434
- You think I never used this before?
- I know you did.

15:06.538 --> 15:08.972
Then you know I'll shoot
this whole motherfucker up then.

15:09.074 --> 15:12.475
But you ain't got to use it tonight.
If he foolish enough to come after you

15:12.578 --> 15:15.376
I'll put the bullet in him my damn self.

15:22.054 --> 15:24.352
You a crazy motherfucker, Mud.

15:25.457 --> 15:27.220
Run, motherfucker! Run!

15:27.326 --> 15:29.294
You can get out of here, too.

15:29.395 --> 15:31.192
I'll talk this peckerwood
into not calling the police.

15:31.297 --> 15:32.423
Oh, okay.

15:33.299 --> 15:35.529
Sorry about that, chief.

15:39.939 --> 15:41.634
Sorry about the damage, boss.

15:41.740 --> 15:44.174
Yeah, you fucked up my place. You...

15:44.276 --> 15:46.506
Yes, sir. It's a damn shame, boss.

15:46.612 --> 15:48.512
Just get out.

15:52.151 --> 15:54.051
Here. There you go.

15:54.687 --> 15:56.348
Appreciate it.

15:58.190 --> 15:59.919
Fucked up my shit.

16:02.127 --> 16:04.755
Ain't never see them pitchers?
Here's how you do it.

16:04.863 --> 16:07.491
When you get that ball,
you gonna kick that leg over.

16:07.599 --> 16:10.796
You gonna throw that thing
way up there like that.

16:10.903 --> 16:13.235
Been looking all over for you.

16:15.040 --> 16:16.405
We're just here working, sir.

16:16.508 --> 16:18.100
I thought we was all right, boss.

16:18.210 --> 16:21.509
Stop talking to me
like I'm some damn plantation owner.

16:21.613 --> 16:23.843
What the fuck you want then?

16:25.517 --> 16:27.382
I want to put you on a record.

16:27.486 --> 16:29.420
- A record?
- Yeah, that's right.

16:29.521 --> 16:30.920
You're kidding.

16:31.023 --> 16:32.547
No, sir, boss.

16:36.595 --> 16:39.120
Let me get this straight now.

16:39.231 --> 16:43.167
We shoot up half your whole joint,
and now you want to put us on a record.

16:43.268 --> 16:45.168
Yeah, that's right.

16:45.270 --> 16:47.636
I hear good things about you.

16:47.740 --> 16:50.800
- When do you want to do this?
- Right now. The studio's booked.

16:50.909 --> 16:53.605
- But I got to get my band.
- No, you don't.

16:53.712 --> 16:56.738
Not the crazy harp-playing motherfucker,
you don't. No. Just you.

16:56.849 --> 16:58.680
You want to do this?

16:59.318 --> 17:01.252
- Yeah.
- Come on. Studio's booked.

17:01.353 --> 17:05.449
<i>Well, I'm going away to leave</i>
<i>Won't be back no more</i>

17:06.125 --> 17:08.388
<i>Going back down south, child...</i>

17:08.894 --> 17:12.386
<i>Now, Leonard Chess didn't</i>
<i>worry none about skin color.</i>

17:12.998 --> 17:15.262
<i>It was the color of them
bills that mattered.</i>

17:16.135 --> 17:18.660
<i>Just get you enough
green to cover yourself</i>

17:18.936 --> 17:21.701
<i>and then you ain't
no Jew-boy no more.</i>

17:22.007 --> 17:24.531
<i>And you ain't no
colored boy either.</i>

17:24.877 --> 17:26.902
<i>You're just a man with a Cadillac.</i>

17:27.012 --> 17:28.172
It's so beautiful!

17:30.549 --> 17:33.712
- Do we have enough?
- Hi, baby. Stop with the "enough."

17:33.819 --> 17:36.219
This is America. The word is "more."

17:36.321 --> 17:38.221
I like the way your husband thinks.

17:38.323 --> 17:40.553
You must be Muddy.

17:40.659 --> 17:43.389
I'm Revetta. I love your record.

17:45.364 --> 17:47.889
Thank you. Pleasure to meet you.

17:49.435 --> 17:52.233
I packed for a week. Will that be enough?

17:52.771 --> 17:54.363
Yeah, that ought to be good.

17:54.473 --> 17:57.840
I think she's asking,
how long are you gonna be gone.

17:58.444 --> 18:00.173
Come here. Hey.

18:00.279 --> 18:02.440
Close your eyes.

18:05.184 --> 18:08.312
A little friend to keep you company
while I'm gone.

18:08.420 --> 18:10.081
There you go.

18:12.825 --> 18:16.659
- Can we afford this?
- Don't worry about it. It's classy.

18:17.262 --> 18:18.229
Thank you.

18:19.998 --> 18:22.432
I tell you, that's a whole lot of ocean.

18:22.534 --> 18:25.628
Take a hell of a lot
to get me to cross it.

18:26.972 --> 18:29.998
How come you didn't stay your ass
in Poland?

18:31.677 --> 18:34.908
How come you didn't stay your ass
in Mississippi?

18:37.649 --> 18:40.812
<i>Len knew the only way</i>
<i>to make it big was radio.</i>

18:41.420 --> 18:45.117
<i>And that meant taking</i>
<i>Muddy back down South.</i>

18:49.061 --> 18:52.155
- Thank you very much.
- The man don't need no more Scotch.

18:59.805 --> 19:02.137
I got a hell of a mortgage.

19:02.841 --> 19:04.172
Shit.

19:04.276 --> 19:06.335
Yeah, I got one of those.

19:06.445 --> 19:08.845
I tell you what.
Throw this record on the table.

19:08.947 --> 19:10.107
It pays off everybody's.

19:10.215 --> 19:11.375
Leonard...

19:11.483 --> 19:14.782
If people buy Muddy's record,
I got to make more.

19:15.420 --> 19:17.615
Then I'm into you every month.

19:17.723 --> 19:19.884
Yeah, but I got to be fair, you know.

19:19.992 --> 19:22.051
I know you got to be fair.

19:22.828 --> 19:27.094
The motherfuckers bring in the
Glenfiddich and the Johnnie Walker.

19:28.133 --> 19:29.862
But you got to ask yourself,

19:29.968 --> 19:33.096
do they really stand up
to Jackson and Grant?

19:50.722 --> 19:52.713
I don't bribe deejays.

19:53.625 --> 19:54.785
I do.

19:56.728 --> 19:59.026
You realize he doesn't care
about your music.

19:59.131 --> 20:00.257
It's just about the money with him.

20:00.365 --> 20:04.233
<i>Everybody, this is the newest race
music right out of Chicago.</i>

20:05.704 --> 20:07.604
You're on your own.

20:17.015 --> 20:22.146
<i>Now, in the South, whites and coloreds</i>
<i>didn't ride around in the same car</i>

20:23.021 --> 20:25.683
<i>unless the colored
man was chauffeuring.</i>

20:25.791 --> 20:27.884
Fuck Mississippi police.

20:37.970 --> 20:40.029
You got to bless them.

20:40.138 --> 20:43.005
- All right, easy. Thank you.
- Hey, you gotta bless them.

20:44.176 --> 20:46.667
- It's very good.
- Room service.

20:52.551 --> 20:53.984
Well, hello.

20:54.086 --> 20:56.850
- We heard you on the radio.
- Come on in.

21:01.526 --> 21:04.188
No, he don't bite. And I don't either.

21:06.231 --> 21:07.823
Play it, Daddy.

21:09.101 --> 21:10.625
Yeah.

21:12.204 --> 21:13.694
Don't rush it.

21:15.774 --> 21:19.210
Don't step on it now.
That's Chicago's heartbeat.

21:19.978 --> 21:21.411
Go on, now.

21:24.216 --> 21:26.650
You've got such hair.

21:27.352 --> 21:29.343
Play that for me, Daddy.

21:29.955 --> 21:31.820
I lied to you, girl.

21:31.923 --> 21:33.652
Yeah, I like that.

21:37.829 --> 21:42.596
- Where you going? Don't leave us alone.
- I'll swing one over your way.

21:42.701 --> 21:44.362
I'm married.

21:44.469 --> 21:46.767
Yeah, and they ain't redhead.

21:49.107 --> 21:50.699
That's bullshit.

21:53.345 --> 21:56.974
Yeah, that's right. Come on, Daddy.
Come on back.

21:57.616 --> 21:59.811
Preacher lay his Bible down.

22:02.788 --> 22:06.121
We're coming straight to you
from down in the Delta

22:08.460 --> 22:11.156
with Muddy Waters and his hit record.

22:11.596 --> 22:13.461
That's right. Sunshine, how you doing?

22:13.565 --> 22:17.729
I want to say a big hello, if I can,
to everybody down in Coahoma County.

22:17.836 --> 22:21.431
They got a whole mess of bluesmen
working Mississippi fields.

22:21.540 --> 22:24.134
When I was out there I used to sing...

22:24.242 --> 22:27.700
<i>Time don't get no better</i>

22:27.813 --> 22:30.145
<i>Up the road I'm going</i>

22:30.415 --> 22:33.942
So, you know,
I want to thank old Len Chess here for

22:34.286 --> 22:36.277
giving Muddy Water a chance to shine.

22:36.388 --> 22:38.583
Does that mean you're staying
where you are?

22:38.690 --> 22:41.352
Because I know some labels down here
who'd love to snap you up.

22:41.460 --> 22:45.954
Well, they can try all they want to,
but I belong to the Chess family.

22:46.765 --> 22:48.790
We're gonna play a little something
from Muddy Waters right now.

22:48.900 --> 22:49.389
Lay it on me.

22:50.769 --> 22:53.533
It was kind, what you said on the radio.

22:53.638 --> 22:58.632
You know, starting a business together,
it is like starting a family.

22:58.744 --> 23:00.405
Appreciate that.

23:00.712 --> 23:05.308
Yeah, well, how come, then,
you need me to sign this thing?

23:08.186 --> 23:10.677
That's what people do in business.

23:12.491 --> 23:15.927
You know, you got a
power with that guitar.

23:16.928 --> 23:20.489
Amazing. It even put three women
in your bed last night.

23:20.599 --> 23:22.567
Yeah, but you married.

23:22.667 --> 23:25.761
I like another kind of broad.
Does that bother you?

23:25.871 --> 23:27.099
What's that gonna bother me for?

23:27.205 --> 23:31.403
I'm just saying, it doesn't make me
like them. And that's not me.

23:31.510 --> 23:33.137
I'm not that.

23:34.513 --> 23:36.071
Who is you?

23:37.349 --> 23:39.613
Sign the contract and find out.

23:40.952 --> 23:42.146
You got a pen there?

23:42.254 --> 23:43.585
All right.

23:43.688 --> 23:46.953
This is the newest race music
right out of Chicago.

23:48.093 --> 23:50.561
And I want you to remember this name.

23:50.662 --> 23:52.220
Muddy Waters.

23:53.265 --> 23:56.257
The last time I signed something
like this, I got married.

23:56.368 --> 23:58.700
Well, that's what this is.

23:58.804 --> 24:00.772
Till death do us part.

24:04.543 --> 24:07.376
By the way, the car's yours.

