51:24.748 --> 51:28.582
Enough! What you need to do
is get back to the Pepsi-Cola, boy.

51:28.685 --> 51:31.677
Let me tell you,
that liquor ain't for you.

51:31.788 --> 51:34.552
What you gonna do, Mud?
You gonna hit me, Mud?

51:34.658 --> 51:37.388
You gonna choke me now? On the street?

51:38.628 --> 51:40.186
Get off me.

51:43.400 --> 51:44.867
You know,

51:45.702 --> 51:47.169
that Wolf,

51:49.039 --> 51:51.735
the way he stood up for his sideman,

51:53.743 --> 51:56.371
maybe he could teach you something, Mud.

52:00.784 --> 52:02.479
Esther, come on!

52:06.256 --> 52:08.918
Find yourself another harp player.

52:17.567 --> 52:20.035
<i>Well, baby, you know</i>
<i>I can never be satisfied</i>

52:20.303 --> 52:23.739
<i>And I just can't keep from crying</i>

52:25.742 --> 52:27.300
<i>Lay it on, man.</i>

52:35.919 --> 52:38.410
<i>Hubert Sumlin,
ladies and gentlemen.</i>

53:04.447 --> 53:07.109
- What you want, miss?
- Tell Pot that I ain't leaving.

53:07.217 --> 53:09.549
Pot! Your girl said she ain't leaving.

53:09.653 --> 53:13.316
I want your things out of my room
when I get home. I told you.

53:18.061 --> 53:21.155
You can't hide from the eye of God.

53:21.998 --> 53:23.966
He hunting heads tonight.

53:38.448 --> 53:41.906
Muddy, I don't think
I want to be in your band no more.

53:43.220 --> 53:45.347
You steal him from me again,

53:46.690 --> 53:48.180
I'll kill you.

53:54.197 --> 53:55.357
He tell you I quit?

53:55.465 --> 53:58.730
He said he felt like
somebody took away his oxygen.

54:01.004 --> 54:02.198
Walter.

54:03.940 --> 54:05.430
You're family.

54:06.643 --> 54:08.634
You don't have to do this.

54:12.616 --> 54:14.311
I'm gonna miss you.

54:33.403 --> 54:38.534
<i>When you lose that cat that gave you</i>
<i>that sound that nobody else could,</i>

54:40.043 --> 54:41.271
<i>it hurts.</i>

54:41.378 --> 54:43.778
<i>Hurts more than losing your woman.</i>

54:56.760 --> 54:58.728
It's good you brought him in.

54:58.828 --> 55:00.921
See what I was telling you, baby?

55:01.031 --> 55:02.658
He's different.

55:02.766 --> 55:05.530
I don't know, Len.
He sound a little country to me.

55:05.635 --> 55:07.535
Maybe we blues him up just a little bit.

55:07.637 --> 55:08.797
Willie.

55:09.506 --> 55:12.805
I don't want you to blues this up.
This ain't the blues.

55:12.909 --> 55:16.367
I don't know what the fuck it is,
but we're gonna record it.

55:16.479 --> 55:18.106
- There you go, baby.
- Yeah.

55:35.832 --> 55:38.596
Hey. Hey there, girl.

55:40.370 --> 55:41.667
Tell Chess

55:44.107 --> 55:45.734
I need a new car.

55:46.976 --> 55:48.807
This ain't the right color.

55:54.250 --> 55:55.911
You got something real special.

55:56.019 --> 55:59.352
Thank you, Mr. Freed. Thank you.
Thank you very much.

56:01.891 --> 56:03.324
Do you think you'll be able to play it?

56:03.426 --> 56:07.556
If I play it, I make
you famous and him rich.

56:07.664 --> 56:10.792
The question is, how bad do you want it?

56:10.900 --> 56:14.927
I'm sorry.
You said, me famous and him rich? Yeah?

56:15.372 --> 56:18.967
Well, hold on. One second. One second.

56:19.075 --> 56:21.475
Let me switch sides
with you for a moment.

56:21.578 --> 56:23.239
Chuck's a bit of a comedian.

56:24.514 --> 56:26.106
- Well, this is nice.
- Yeah.

56:26.216 --> 56:28.810
- This is very nice.
- I'm sure we can work something out.

56:28.918 --> 56:32.183
Now, some of you people
might call this race music.

56:32.288 --> 56:36.122
I call it rock and roll, and it's
too fun for anybody to sit out on,

56:36.226 --> 56:37.887
white or colored.

56:39.262 --> 56:41.560
- Did he just say what I think he said?
- Yeah.

56:41.664 --> 56:44.258
He just integrated the airwaves.

56:44.367 --> 56:48.303
- Here we are.
- Here we are, motherfucker. Here we are.

56:48.405 --> 56:51.306
- Oh, God.
- Mr. Waters, I am deeply grateful to you.

56:51.408 --> 56:52.705
You got it, baby.

57:09.192 --> 57:11.717
<i>Riding along in my automobile</i>

57:12.962 --> 57:15.487
<i>I was anxious to tell
her the way I feel</i>

57:16.433 --> 57:19.027
<i>So I told her softly and sincere</i>

57:19.135 --> 57:21.763
<i>Chuck was playing in
segregated cities.</i>

57:24.340 --> 57:29.039
<i>But there was just a thin rope</i>
<i>to separate coloreds from whites.</i>

57:29.779 --> 57:31.838
<i>And a whole lot of history.</i>

57:42.058 --> 57:45.186
<i>And that's all it took
to bring us all together,</i>

57:45.295 --> 57:48.287
<i>one man duck-walking across stage.</i>

57:48.398 --> 57:49.490
<i>Shit.</i>

57:51.234 --> 57:53.429
Please keep the aisles clear.

57:54.838 --> 57:56.135
Get back over here.

57:56.239 --> 57:58.036
Keep the aisles clear.

58:16.125 --> 58:17.683
Why don't you play like that, Daddy?

58:17.794 --> 58:21.355
- Ain't nothing but the blues sped up.
- It's rock and roll.

58:23.132 --> 58:24.759
Look at that car!

58:27.804 --> 58:29.829
Len Chess got two hot cars.

58:31.074 --> 58:33.099
Hey, Muddy. Hey, Charles.

58:33.209 --> 58:35.734
We're on <i>American Bandstand.</i>
You believe this?

58:35.845 --> 58:39.281
- There's the man. Been a long time.
- Chuck Berry!

58:39.382 --> 58:41.907
- Hey, is this the boy?
- Yeah, that's Charles.

58:42.018 --> 58:43.315
That's your car outside?

58:43.419 --> 58:44.886
The cherry-red one out there?

58:44.988 --> 58:46.956
It's the most beautiful
thing I've ever seen.

58:47.056 --> 58:49.422
Ain't it? Good taste.

58:49.526 --> 58:52.654
- Sit down, Charles. Have a seat.
- Chuck Berry.

58:53.296 --> 58:55.924
Charles, Charlie, Chuck.

58:56.466 --> 58:59.435
Mortgage payment
and child support killing me.

59:00.203 --> 59:02.797
And I ain't booking the clubs enough.

59:04.874 --> 59:07.502
Len, I was talking to the accountant,

59:08.578 --> 59:10.409
and he been telling me
I'm borrowing against my royalties.

59:10.513 --> 59:13.004
Len, Mud, it's coming.
You're gonna miss it.

59:13.116 --> 59:14.242
Yeah. In a minute.

59:14.350 --> 59:17.615
What's going on?
I thought I was just getting paid.

59:21.858 --> 59:23.689
Records ain't selling.

59:24.193 --> 59:27.993
Is that how come you got
a brand-new Cadillac in the driveway?

59:28.731 --> 59:30.756
He bought me that Cadillac.

59:31.968 --> 59:34.960
Me, you and every other motherfucker

59:35.071 --> 59:38.700
cashes a Chess Records check
is riding that man's coattails.

59:38.808 --> 59:40.537
And that ain't good.

59:41.377 --> 59:42.366
Thank you.

59:42.478 --> 59:45.345
In my book, you're still number one.

59:46.049 --> 59:47.539
You, too, baby.

59:47.884 --> 59:50.079
Hey, Dad, you got to see this.

01:00:03.466 --> 01:00:07.960
<i>They were locking up fine black
women for sitting on buses,</i>

